premise_source_doc_sentence: Jemaine Clement  (  born 10 January 1974  )  is a New Zealand comedian , actor , voice actor , singer , writer , director , and multi-instrumentalist , known as one half of the musical comedy duo Flight of the Conchords along with Bret McKenzie .
In 2009 he directed Diagnosis : Death , a feature film starring Jemaine Clement , Bret McKenzie and Rhys Darby  (  of Flight of the Conchords fame  )  .
The film has received recent notoriety for co-starring and being co-written by Jemaine Clement , star of the HBO comedy Flight of the Conchords .
The show has received 10 Emmy Award nominations , including `` Outstanding Comedy Series '' and `` Outstanding Lead Actor in a Comedy Series '' for Jemaine Clement , both in 2009 .
Jemaine Clement and Bret McKenzie of the band Flight of the Conchords star as fictional versions of themselves .
It also features songs written by Jemaine Clement and Bret McKenzie - also from the Flight of the Conchords .
